in jmeter integration with jenkins with docker will it generate an report with graphs in jenkins & can we download it?


Yes, integrating JMeter with Jenkins and Docker will allow you to generate reports with graphs that can be viewed and downloaded directly within Jenkins

Report Generation & Visualisation
Performance Trend Graphs: By using the Jenkins Performance Plugin, Jenkins can parse JMeter result files (usually .jtl or .xml) to generate performance trend charts and throughput graphs.
HTML Dashboard Reports: JMeter can be configured to generate its native HTML Dashboard Report during the test run using the -g (generate) and -o (output directory) flags.
Jenkins Display: To view these HTML reports within Jenkins, you must use the HTML Publisher Plugin. Note that you may need to adjust the Jenkins Content Security Policy (CSP) to allow the graphs and CSS to display correctly. 
