Downloading Reports
Build Artifacts: You can configure your Jenkins job to archive artifacts at the end of the build. This allows you to download the entire HTML report folder (as a ZIP) or the raw .jtl data files directly from the build page.
Docker Considerations: When running JMeter inside a Docker container, ensure the container's output directory is mapped to the Jenkins Workspace using volumes (e.g., -v $WORKSPACE:/results). This ensures the generated report files persist on the Jenkins agent after the container terminates. 
